    <string name="tutorial_welcome_headline">Welcome to Aura</string>
    <string name="tutorial_welcome_text">
    This is a beta version, please expect a few bumps on the road :)
    \n
    \n⦿ Aura doesn\'t use the internet
    \n⦿ Bluetooth must be enabled
    \n⦿ It needs no SIM card or Wifi
    \n
    \nAura works on factory-reset phones, on planes and of course on Mars.
    \n
    \nThe following tutorial explains how things work.
    </string>
    <string name="tutorial_enabled_headline">Turn Aura on/off</string>
    <string name="tutorial_enabled_text">
        You\'re always in control of your Aura\'s visibility.
        \n
        \nBecause it doesn\'t use internet or GPS, Aura protects your privacy and doesn\'t drain your battery (0.1% per day).
        \n
        \nDon\'t worry to keep Aura always on, it was built for that.
    </string>
    <plurals name="tutorial_color_text">
        <item quantity="zero">
            Your Aura consists of your name and text.
            \n
            \nClick the colored square to pick the color in which others will see your Aura.
        </item>
        <item quantity="one">
            Your Aura consists of your name, text and an idea that you care for.
            \n
            \nClick the colored square to pick the color in which others will see your Aura.
        </item>
        <item quantity="other">
            Your Aura consists of your name, text and up to %d ideas that you care for.
            \n
            \nClick the colored square to pick the color in which others will see your Aura.
        </item>
    </plurals>
    <string name="tutorial_color_headline">Color your Aura</string>
    <string name="tutorial_name_headline">Choose a Name</string>
    <string name="tutorial_name_text">
        Click to enter a nickname, a pseudonym or your real name.
        \n
        \nLike the rest of your Aura this will be visible to Aura users around you. You can change it any time.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_text_headline">Add your Text</string>
    <string name="tutorial_text_text">
        Share information about yourself or something you care for.
        \nYou can add links to social media and websites.
    </string>
    <string name="tutorial_slogan_add_headline">Add an Idea</string>
    <string name="tutorial_slogan_add_text">An idea is everything worth sharing with nearby Aura users.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_slogan_edit_headline">Your Ideas</string>
    <string name="tutorial_slogan_edit_text">This is a list of your ideas. Click each to delete or edit it.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_swipe_headline">◀︎ Swipe left and right ▶︎</string>
    <string name="tutorial_swipe_text">You can swipe to move between your own Aura and a list of nearby Auras.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_adopt_headline">Check out others</string>
    <string name="tutorial_adopt_text">Click a name to see the profile text. Press and hold an idea to add it to your Aura.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_final_headline">Final Words</string>
    <string name="tutorial_final_text">
        Sometimes it\'s important to deny having used Aura and quickly purging all your data.
        \n
        \nFor this, Aura supports the panic button Ripple (getAura.io/ripple).
        \n\nIn the Aura settings you can make sure all data is purged.
    </string>
